            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-03-27T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-03-27T20:00:00-05:00" n="97" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d97">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">851G.00/3–2847: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Vice Consul at Hanoi</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">O’Sullivan</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hanoi</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-03-28T08:00:00+07:00">March 28, 1947—8 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>110. According French monitoring service, Radio Vietnam 26 March states Giam Made
                    following declaration upon assuming office minister Foreign Affairs: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“I continue faithfully president Ho’s policy with democratic peoples of
                            world and primarily with people of France. We have no race hatred and we
                            accept independence of Vietnam in frame work French Union.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>This Statement seems designed to enforce impression that Giam is “moderate” with
                    whom French might deal. Coming on eve of Bollaert’s arrival in Indochina, it
                    appears to indicate Vietnamese are not unwilling negotiate.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">O’Sullivan</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
